NAME
       getline, getdelim - read a delimited line from a stream

SYNOPSIS
       #include <stdio.h>

       ssize_t getline(char **lineptr, size_t *n, FILE *stream);
       ssize_t getdelim(char **lineptr, size_t *n, int delim,
                        FILE *stream);

DESCRIPTION
       Reads from stream up to and including the next delimiter
       character ('\\n' for getline; any byte for getdelim). The line
       is stored in *lineptr, which is grown with realloc as needed; n
       is updated to the new capacity.

       If *lineptr is NULL on entry, a buffer is allocated; the caller
       must free it eventually.

RETURN VALUE
       Number of bytes read (including the delimiter), or -1 on EOF or
       error.

SEE ALSO
       fgets(3), fopen(3)
